Richard Graham wrote:<BR>
&gt; What: &nbsp;Change the mpicc/mpicxx/mpif77/mpif90 from being binaries to being<BR>
&gt; shell scripts<BR>
&gt;<BR>
&gt; Why: Our build environment assumes that wrapper compilers will use the same<BR>
&gt; binary format that the Open MPI libraries do. &nbsp;In cross-compile environment,<BR>
&gt; the MPI wrapper compilers will run on the front-end and need to run on the<BR>
&gt; front-end, and not the back-end. &nbsp;Jeff has suggested this as the simplest<BR>
&gt; way to build back-end libraries, and front-end wrapper-compilers.<BR>
&gt;<BR>
&gt; When: within the next several weeks (for the 1.3 release)<BR>
&gt;<BR>
&gt; Timeout: 10/19/2007<BR>
&gt;<BR>
&gt;<BR>
&gt; Rich<BR>
